lead_paragraph: BELGRADE, Yugoslavia, Feb. 28 -- Having completed his negotiations in Turkey, the British Foreign Secretary, Anthony Eden, will shortly visit Athens to round out Britain's system of alliances in the Balkans and the Near East and to develop the existing pacts between Turkey, Greece and Britain into a tripartite entente, according to diplomatic sources here.
abstract: Foreign Min A Eden and Gen Sir J Dill en route to Athens
